mption on resource-rich countries, he argues that there is a way to consume responsibly and alleviate global poverty.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aConservation of natural resources. 0aConsumption (Economics)xEnvironmental aspects. 0aConsumption (Economics)xMoral and ethical aspects. 0aEnvironmental policy. 0aNatural resourcesxEnvironmental aspects. 0aRaw materialsxEnvironmental aspects. 0aSustainable development. 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831105379940 cprintz978030014161040uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030015567940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300155679423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300155679/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY